                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="atlanta_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">the capital city of the US state of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/georgia" title="Georgia definition"><span class="ndv">Georgia</span></a>. It is a major commercial centre for the south-eastern US. <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/martin-luther-king" title="Martin Luther King definition"><span class="ndv">Martin Luther King</span></a> led the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-civil-rights-movement" title="civil rights movement definition"><span class="ndv">civil rights movement</span></a> from Atlanta. The 1996 Olympic Games were also held there.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
